  <text>
    <style color="0xaaaaaa">(Pure dust is an intermediary product in the processing of ores, see the ore processing tab in JEI/REI/EMI for any ore's specific processing steps)</style>
  </text>
  <br></br>
  <text>Pure dust is obtained from either <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:machines/macerator" underlined="true">macerating</style> or <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:machines/forge_hammer" underlined="true">forge hammering</style> <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:materials/purified_ore" underlined="true">Purified ore</style>, to obtain byproducts from processing Purified ore into Pure Dust it has to be macerated, the chance to get a byproduct increases with the tier of the macerator. <br></br> Pure dust can be further processed by <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:machines/centrifuge" underlined="true">centrifuging</style> or <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:machines/ore_washer" underlined="true">washing</style> it, for byproducts it has to be centrifuged.</text>
